                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>List of tributes or register of land parcels (?).  It lists some revenues (mostly honeycombs) from lands followed by the names of individuals who paid them. 
                              The note is written in a mediocre but careful hand. Some parts are illegible due to faded ink.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="ti">ኍልቆ፡ እርሻ፡ ዘባን፡ ጨአ፡ ፩ገራ፡ ክፉእ፡ ወድቅጽው፡ ፩ገራብ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="2r" to="2v"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Excerpt from <title ref="LIT2278salota"/> and <title ref="LIT2703salota"/>.  They are written in <ref target="h1">Hand 1</ref>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#140r"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">The note states that <persName ref="PRS15310WalattaTakHay">Walatta Takla Hāymānot</persName> and her mother <persName ref="PRS15307AmataMikael">ʾAmata Mikāʾel</persName>
                              bought the manuscript and donated it to the church <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM">Kidāna Mǝḥrat Māy ʾAnbasā</placeName>. 
                              It also mentions their spiritual fathers. Two other spiritual (?) fathers are mentioned above the note. The note is written in red ink by the same secondary hand as that in <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmakm002#a2">Ms. MAKM-002, Additio 2</ref>. 
                              These individuals are also mentioned in <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmakm002#a2">Ms. MAKM-002, Additio 2</ref>.
                              The handwriting is mediocre, characterized by angular letters. <persName ref="PRS15310WalattaTakHay">Walatta Takla Hāymānot</persName> and her sister <persName ref="PRS15309SabanaGiyorgis">Sabana Giyorgis</persName> appear in a brief supplication written at the top of the donation note by another
                              secondary hand. The note is separated from the main text by chains of black and red dots, with nine-dot asterisks in between.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"><hi rend="rubric">ዝመፅሐፍ፡ ዘወለተ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ አመተ፡ ሚካኤል: ዘተሳየጠት፡ በወርቅ። ወሃበታ፡ ለኪዳነ፡ ምረት፡  ዘማየ<sic/>፡ አንበሳ። ወአቡሐ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ 
                              ስላሴ፡ ወእማ፡ እግዚ፡ ሐረያ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ አቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ሚካኤል።<add place="above">አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ስላሴ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡</add>
                              <add place="above">መሐረኒ፡ ወተሣሃለኒ፡ ለዓመትከ፡ ሰበነ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለተ፡ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</add></hi></q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The title, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዳዊት</foreign>, is written on the front board with blue paint.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#85r"/>
                           <desc>Shelfmark C4-IV-65</desc> 
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>The Psalms are divided into groups of 10 by means of a chain of red and black dots.</desc>
